## Comprehensive Report: Vercel AI SDK Provider Package Structure

I've completed a thorough exploration of the provider package structure and build setup in the Vercel AI SDK monorepo. Here are my findings:

### 1. FULL DIRECTORY LISTING - Representative Provider (black-forest-labs - Image Generation Only)

**File Structure:**
```
packages/black-forest-labs/
├── CHANGELOG.md
├── README.md
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
├── tsconfig.build.json
├── turbo.json
├── tsup.config.ts
├── vitest.node.config.js
├── vitest.edge.config.js
└── src/
    ├── index.ts
    ├── version.ts
    ├── black-forest-labs-provider.ts
    ├── black-forest-labs-provider.test.ts
    ├── black-forest-labs-image-model.ts
    ├── black-forest-labs-image-model.test.ts
    └── black-forest-labs-image-settings.ts
```

**More Complex Example (openai - Multiple Capabilities):**
```
packages/openai/
├── CHANGELOG.md
├── README.md
├── internal.d.ts
├── package.json
├── tsconfig.json
├── tsconfig.build.json
├── turbo.json
├── tsup.config.ts
├── vitest.node.config.js
├── vitest.edge.config.js
└── src/
    ├── index.ts
    ├── version.ts
    ├── openai-provider.ts
    ├── openai-provider.test.ts
    ├── openai-config.ts
    ├── openai-error.ts
    ├── openai-tools.ts
    ├── openai-language-model-capabilities.ts
    ├── chat/
    │   ├── openai-chat-language-model.ts
    │   ├── openai-chat-language-model.test.ts
    │   ├── openai-chat-api.ts
    │   ├── openai-chat-options.ts
    │   ├── openai-chat-prompt.ts
    │   ├── openai-chat-prepare-tools.ts
    │   ├── __fixtures__/
    │   └── __snapshots__/
    ├── completion/
    ├── embedding/
    ├── image/
    ├── responses/
    ├── speech/
    ├── tool/
    ├── transcription/
    ├── internal/
    └── responses/
```

---

### 2. PACKAGE.JSON STRUCTURE

**Standard Provider Pattern:**
```json
{
  "name": "@ai-sdk/{provider-name}",
  "version": "X.Y.Z",
  "license": "Apache-2.0",
  "sideEffects": false,
  "main": "./dist/index.js",
  "module": "./dist/index.mjs",
  "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",

  "files": [
    "dist/**/*",
    "docs/**/*",
    "src",
    "!src/**/*.test.ts",
    "!src/**/*.test-d.ts",
    "!src/**/__snapshots__",
    "!src/**/__fixtures__",
    "CHANGELOG.md",
    "README.md"
  ],

  "directories": {
    "doc": "./docs"
  },

  "scripts": {
    "build": "pnpm clean && tsup --tsconfig tsconfig.build.json",
    "build:watch": "pnpm clean && tsup --watch",
    "clean": "del-cli dist docs *.tsbuildinfo",
    "prepack": "mkdir -p docs && cp ../../content/providers/.../XX-provider-name.mdx ./docs/",
    "postpack": "del-cli docs",
    "type-check": "tsc --build",
    "test": "pnpm test:node && pnpm test:edge",
    "test:update": "pnpm test:node -u",
    "test:watch": "vitest --config vitest.node.config.js",
    "test:edge": "vitest --config vitest.edge.config.js --run",
    "test:node": "vitest --config vitest.node.config.js --run"
  },

  "exports": {
    "./package.json": "./package.json",
    ".": {
      "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
      "import": "./dist/index.mjs",
      "require": "./dist/index.js"
    },
    "./internal": {  // Optional, for complex providers like openai
      "types": "./dist/internal/index.d.ts",
      "import": "./dist/internal/index.mjs",
      "module": "./dist/internal/index.mjs",
      "require": "./dist/internal/index.js"
    }
  },

  "dependencies": {
    "@ai-sdk/provider": "workspace:*",
    "@ai-sdk/provider-utils": "workspace:*"
  },

  "devDependencies": {
    "@ai-sdk/test-server": "workspace:*",
    "@types/node": "20.17.24",
    "@vercel/ai-tsconfig": "workspace:*",
    "tsup": "^8",
    "typescript": "5.8.3",
    "zod": "3.25.76"
  },

  "peerDependencies": {
    "zod": "^3.25.76 || ^4.1.8"
  },

  "engines": {
    "node": ">=18"
  },

  "publishConfig": {
    "access": "public"
  },

  "homepage": "https://ai-sdk.dev/docs",
  "repository": {
    "type": "git",
    "url": "git+https://github.com/vercel/ai.git"
  },
  "bugs": {
    "url": "https://github.com/vercel/ai/issues"
  },
  "keywords": ["ai"]
}
```

**Key Dependencies:**
- `@ai-sdk/provider`: Base types and interfaces (ProviderV3, LanguageModelV3, ImageModelV3, etc.)
- `@ai-sdk/provider-utils`: Utilities for API calls, headers, key loading, etc.

---

### 3. TSCONFIG.JSON STRUCTURE

**Standard Provider tsconfig.json:**
```json
{
  "extends": "./node_modules/@vercel/ai-tsconfig/ts-library.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "composite": true,
    "rootDir": "src",
    "outDir": "dist"
  },
  "exclude": [
    "dist",
    "build",
    "node_modules",
    "tsup.config.ts",
    "internal.d.ts"  // Only for providers with internal exports
  ],
  "references": [
    { "path": "../provider" },
    { "path": "../provider-utils" },
    { "path": "../test-server" }  // Optional, only if using test-server
  ]
}
```

**tsconfig.build.json (used during build):**
```json
{
  "extends": "./tsconfig.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "composite": false  // Disable composite for tsup builds
  }
}
```

**Root tsconfig.json Pattern:**
The monorepo's root tsconfig.json references all packages via the TypeScript `references` field:
```json
{
  "references": [
    { "path": "packages/ai" },
    { "path": "packages/openai" },
    { "path": "packages/anthropic" },
    { "path": "packages/provider" },
    { "path": "packages/provider-utils" },
    // ... 50+ more packages
  ],
  "include": []
}
```

This enables incremental type-checking across the monorepo via `tsc --build`.

---

### 4. MAIN ENTRY POINT ORGANIZATION

**Minimal Image Generation Provider (black-forest-labs):**
```typescript
// src/index.ts
export {
  createBlackForestLabs,
  blackForestLabs,
} from './black-forest-labs-provider';
export type {
  BlackForestLabsProvider,
  BlackForestLabsProviderSettings,
} from './black-forest-labs-provider';
export type {
  BlackForestLabsImageModelId,
  BlackForestLabsAspectRatio,
} from './black-forest-labs-image-settings';
export type {
  BlackForestLabsImageModelOptions,
  BlackForestLabsImageModelOptions as BlackForestLabsImageProviderOptions,
} from './black-forest-labs-image-model';
export { VERSION } from './version';
```

**Complex Multi-Feature Provider (openai):**
```typescript
// src/index.ts
export { createOpenAI, openai } from './openai-provider';
export type { OpenAIProvider, OpenAIProviderSettings } from './openai-provider';
export type {
  OpenAILanguageModelResponsesOptions,
  OpenAILanguageModelResponsesOptions as OpenAIResponsesProviderOptions,
} from './responses/openai-responses-options';
export type {
  OpenAILanguageModelChatOptions,
  OpenAILanguageModelChatOptions as OpenAIChatLanguageModelOptions,
} from './chat/openai-chat-options';
export type { OpenAILanguageModelCompletionOptions } from './completion/openai-completion-options';
export type { OpenAIEmbeddingModelOptions } from './embedding/openai-embedding-options';
export type { OpenAISpeechModelOptions } from './speech/openai-speech-options';
export type { OpenAITranscriptionModelOptions } from './transcription/openai-transcription-options';
export type {
  OpenaiResponsesProviderMetadata,
  OpenaiResponsesReasoningProviderMetadata,
  // ...
} from './responses/openai-responses-provider-metadata';
export { VERSION } from './version';
```

**Provider Pattern:**
- Always export a `createProviderName()` function and `providerName` singleton
- Export provider and settings types
- Export capability-specific option types (ChatOptions, EmbeddingOptions, etc.)
- Export VERSION constant
- Use consistent naming: `{ProviderName}Provider`, `{ProviderName}ProviderSettings`
- Support deprecation aliases in exports for backwards compatibility

---

### 5. ROOT TSCONFIG REFERENCE PATTERN

```json
{
  "references": [
    { "path": "packages/ai" },
    { "path": "packages/mcp" },
    { "path": "packages/alibaba" },
    { "path": "packages/amazon-bedrock" },
    // ... all 56 packages listed
  ],
  "include": []
}
```

**Key Points:**
- All packages are listed as references for monorepo-wide type checking
- The root `"include": []` is intentional (excludes root from compilation)
- Enables `tsc --build` for incremental compilation across all packages
- Composite mode (`composite: true`) in each package enables this pattern

---

### 6. BUILD CONFIGURATION

**tsup.config.ts Pattern (Simple - image generation only):**
```typescript
import { defineConfig } from 'tsup';

export default defineConfig([
  {
    entry: ['src/index.ts'],
    format: ['cjs', 'esm'],
    dts: true,
    sourcemap: true,
    define: {
      __PACKAGE_VERSION__: JSON.stringify(
        (await import('./package.json', { with: { type: 'json' } })).default.version,
      ),
    },
  },
]);
```

**tsup.config.ts Pattern (Complex - multiple entry points):**
```typescript
import { defineConfig } from 'tsup';

export default defineConfig([
  {
    entry: ['src/index.ts'],
    format: ['cjs', 'esm'],
    dts: true,
    sourcemap: true,
    define: {
      __PACKAGE_VERSION__: JSON.stringify(
        (await import('./package.json', { with: { type: 'json' } })).default.version,
      ),
    },
  },
  {
    entry: ['src/internal/index.ts'],
    outDir: 'dist/internal',
    format: ['cjs', 'esm'],
    dts: true,
    sourcemap: true,
    define: {
      __PACKAGE_VERSION__: JSON.stringify(...),
    },
  },
]);
```

**Build Outputs:**
- Dual format: CommonJS (`*.js`) and ES Modules (`*.mjs`)
- Type definitions: `*.d.ts` files generated by `dts: true`
- Sourcemaps: `*.map` files for debugging
- Version injection: `__PACKAGE_VERSION__` constant replaced at build time

---

### 7. VITEST CONFIGURATION

**vitest.node.config.js (Node.js environment):**
```javascript
import { defineConfig } from 'vite';
import packageJson from './package.json';

